wikipedia_page.main: Jonathan Philip Webb (born 5 January 1990) is an English footballer, who made one appearance for Leeds United in 2008 during the F.A. Cup First Round clash with Northampton Town at Elland Road.

link_mentions.page: St Aidan's Church of England High School
response: Jonathan Webb was a pupil at this school between 2001–2008 and an integral part of the football team's success in the North Yorkshire School Football circuit and at National level. He now plays for Loughborough University FC after a brief professional career at Leeds United and Newcastle Blue Star.
